 <author> Ger van Diepen </author>
 <date> 2000/05/31 </date>
 <avers> 1.4 </avers>
 <area> Library </area>
 <package> casa </package>
 <module> Inputs </module>
 <type> Code </type>
 <category> New </category>
 <defects>  </defects>
 <summary>
Added support of --help and --version
 </summary>
 <description>
If the command line consists of the string <code>-v</code> or
<code>--version</code> the program name and version will be printed
and the program is ended.
<br>If the command line consists of the string <code>-h</code> or
<code>--help</code> the program name and version and all parameter
names with their type, default, and explanation will be printed.
<p>
It is useful to show the available parameters if the user has
forgotten them.
 </description>
</change>
